 Omotoso faces 22 charges related to contravening the Sexual Offences Act with two definite charges of rape contained in the charge sheet.He was arrested in April this year.Omotoso had allegedly trafficked women and girls from various branches of his church and taken them to a house in Umhlanga Rocks KwaZulu-Natal where they were sexually exploited.The Nigerian televangelist is a senior pastor of Jesus Dominion International whose headquarters are in Durban with a Port Elizabeth branch in Govan Mbeki Avenue.